# {{.Name}}

A kit-based service scaffolded via `kit init`.

## Quickstart

```bash
go mod tidy
make run
```

Service listens on `:8080` by default. Try `GET http://localhost:8080/ping`.

## Layout

- `main.go` — entry point; constructs `service.Service` and runs it.
- `configs/routes.yaml` — declarative route table; references handler names.
- `configs/clients.yaml` — declarative outbound HTTP clients (apimap).
- `internal/handlers/` — handler implementations.

## Adding endpoints

```bash
kit add-endpoint GET /tasks tasks.list
```

This appends to `routes.yaml` + generates a handler stub.

## Operations

```bash
make doctor     # runs /preflight checks against a running service
make build      # builds binary into bin/
```

